(2789, 1, '2018-01-23 00:58:16', '2018-01-23 00:58:16', '<p>[vc_section full_width=\"stretch_row\" el_class=\"bg_inner-hero\" css=\".vc_custom_1516139500861{background-image: url(http://localhost:8888/belcosta/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/inner-hero.jpg?id=2795) !important;background-position: center !important;background-repeat: no-repeat !important;background-size: cover !important;}\"][vc_row][vc_column][vc_column_text]</p>\n<h5>SERVICES</h5>\n<h1>Cannabis Analytical Testing</h1>\n<p>[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][/vc_section][vc_section el_class=\"lead-in\"][vc_row][vc_column][vc_column_text]</p>\n<h2>What We Can Do</h2>\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">Here’s a list of services that we provide for our clients.</span></p>\n<p>[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][/vc_section][vc_row full_width=\"stretch_row_content\" el_id=\"service-accordion\"][vc_column][vc_tta_accordion c_icon=\"chevron\" active_section=\"1\"][vc_tta_section title=\"Potency Testing\" tab_id=\"ac1\"][vc_row_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/2\"][vc_column_text]</p>\n<h2>Potency testing is used to measure the amount of THC, CBD, and other cannabinoids in a sample</h2>\n<p>We will use a High Performance Liquid Chromatograph with Diode Array Detector, or HPLC-DAD, which is the common standard in the cannabis testing industry. Our potency method is fully validated and ISO-accredited, and is based on cannabinoid testing methods published by the AHP and AHPA.​[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/2\"][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][vc_row_inner el_class=\".bg_callout\"][vc_column_inner width=\"1/2\"][vc_column_text]</p>\n<h3>We test for the following cannainoids:</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>THC</li>\n<li>THCA</li>\n<li>CBD</li>\n<li>CBDA</li>\n<li>CBN</li>\n<li>THCV​​</li>\n<li>​CBGA</li>\n<li>CBCA</li>\n<li>CBG</li>\n<li>CBC</li>\n<li>delta-8-THC</li>\n</ul>\n<p>[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/2\"][vc_single_image image=\"2813\" img_size=\"full\" alignment=\"center\"][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][/vc_tta_section][vc_tta_section title=\"Microbiological Testing\" tab_id=\"ac2\"][vc_row_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/2\"][vc_column_text]</p>\n<h2>Using the most sophisticated microbiologic screening techniques available to science</h2>\n<p>Quality control measures and testing efforts are absolutely essential to be able to produce safe, consistent, and efficacious cannabis products to the public. Our staff contains nationally renowned experts in the field of cannabis testing who set the standard for accurate testing methods. [/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/2\"][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][vc_row_inner el_class=\".bg_callout\"][vc_column_inner width=\"1/2\"][vc_column_text]</p>\n<h3>We test for the following species:</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>E. Coli</li>\n<li>Salmonella spp</li>\n<li>Aspergillus fumigatus</li>\n<li>Aspergillus flavus</li>\n<li>Aspergillus niger</li>\n<li>Aspergillus terreus</li>\n<li>Total Yeast and Mold</li>\n<li>Total Aerobic Plate Count</li>\n<li>Coliforms</li>\n</ul>\n<p>[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/2\"][vc_single_image image=\"2813\" img_size=\"full\" alignment=\"center\"][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][vc_row_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"2/3\"][vc_column_text]</p>\n<h2>How do we test for these microorganisms?</h2>\n<p>​BelCosta Labs utilizes Medicinal Genomics PathogINDICAtor qPCR platform to extract and subsequently amplify pathogen DNA. This has major advantages over traditional plating due to increased sensitivity and specificity. In particular, this assay targets DNA sequences that are unique to each species of bacteria and fungi preventing any kind of potential false positives. ​[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/3\"][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][vc_row_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"2/3\"][vc_column_text]</p>\n<h6>01</h6>\n<h4>Shiga-toxin producing E. Coli (STEC)</h4>\n<p>​​STECs are a type of disease causing bacteria that produces shiga toxin. The most common of these STECs is the O157:H7 serovar which can produce serious gastrointestinal illness.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/3\"][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][vc_row_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"2/3\"][vc_column_text]</p>\n<h6>02</h6>\n<h4>​Salmonella spp.</h4>\n<p>​​​Salmonella is a group of gram-negative, rod shaped bacteria that cause typhoid fever, gastroenteritis, and other illnesses.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/3\"][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][vc_row_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"2/3\"][vc_column_text]</p>\n<h6>03</h6>\n<h4>Aspergillus spp.</h4>\n<p>​Aspergillus is a type of mold that can cause severe respiratory infection, especially in those with compromised immune systems. The State of California chosen to test for four different pathogenic species of Aspergillus that are known to be found in cannabis. These four species include Aspergillus flavus, Aspergillus fumigatus, Aspergillus niger, and Aspergillus terreus.<br />\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/3\"][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][/vc_tta_section][vc_tta_section title=\"Terpene Testing\" tab_id=\"ac3\"][vc_row_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/2\"][vc_column_text]</p>\n<h2>Terpenes are the naturally occurring aromatic compounds in cannabis that contribute to its unique scent, and may even potentiate the medical benefits.</h2>\n<p>Terpenes have been hypothesized to work in synergy with cannabinoids in what has been referred to in literature as the “entourage effect”. Thus, the quantification of terpene content can be a valuable tool in modulating the effects of cannabinoids like THC and CBD. Our terpene analysis method is fully validated and uses a combination of Headspace Analyzer, Gas Chromatography, and Flame Ionization Detection.​[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/2\"][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][vc_row_inner el_class=\".bg_callout\"][vc_column_inner width=\"1/2\"][vc_column_text]</p>\n<h3>We test for the following terpenes:</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Myrcene</li>\n<li>Beta-Caryophyllene</li>\n<li>Alpha Humulene</li>\n<li>Linalool</li>\n<li>Terpinolene</li>\n<li>Limonene</li>\n<li>Valencene</li>\n<li>Phytol</li>\n</ul>\n<p>[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/2\"][vc_single_image image=\"2813\" img_size=\"full\" alignment=\"center\"][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][/vc_tta_section][vc_tta_section title=\"Pesticide Testing\" tab_id=\"ac4\"][vc_row_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/2\"][vc_column_text]</p>\n<h2>​Pesticides are chemical additives used to prevent insects, fungi, and other organisms from destroying a crop</h2>\n<p>However, they have not been approved for application in cannabis plants by any federal regulatory body such as the EPA or FDA, and most state regulatory agencies such as California and Oregon have mandated limits on their use.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/2\"][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][vc_row_inner el_class=\".bg_callout\"][vc_column_inner width=\"1/2\"][vc_column_text]</p>\n<h3>We test for the following pesticides at the listed levels of detection:</h3>\n<p>[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text][table id=1 /][/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/2\"][vc_single_image image=\"2813\" img_size=\"full\" alignment=\"center\"][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][/vc_tta_section][vc_tta_section title=\"Heavy Metal Testing\" tab_id=\"ac5\"][vc_row_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/2\"][vc_column_text]</p>\n<h2>Cannabis is a bioaccumulating plant that can absorb heavy metals from the soil it is grown in</h2>\n<p>Heavy metals, even in small amounts, can have extremely damaging effects on the human body, ranging from neurotoxicity to birth defects to organ failure.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/2\"][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][vc_row_inner el_class=\".bg_callout\"][vc_column_inner width=\"1/2\"][vc_column_text]</p>\n<h3>California law requires that all cannabis products are tested for the presence of heavy metals</h3>\n<p>​In order to quantify amounts of heavy metals in the parts per million range, we use some of the most advanced technology available by utilizing Inductively Coupled Plasma Mass Spectrometry (ICP-MS).​​<br />\n[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text][table id=2 /][/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/2\"][vc_single_image image=\"2813\" img_size=\"full\" alignment=\"center\"][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][/vc_tta_section][vc_tta_section title=\"Residual Solvent Testing\" tab_id=\"ac6\"][vc_row_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/2\"][vc_column_text]</p>\n<h2>The rise in popularity of extracted cannabis concentrates has been met with concern regarding their effect on public health</h2>\n<p>In order to minimize inherent risk of exposure to chemical solvents used in cannabis extractions, all cannabis concentrate products must be tested for residual solvents. While most alkane solvents are not considered toxic in small amounts, chemical impurities such as benzene can be created as byproducts from chemical manufacturing processes. Residual solvents most accurately testing using Headspace Gas Chromatography with Flame Ionization Detection<br />\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/2\"][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][vc_row_inner el_class=\".bg_callout\"][vc_column_inner width=\"1/2\"][vc_column_text]</p>\n<h3>The following is the ca list for residual solvents and their action limits</h3>\n<p>[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text][table id=3 /][/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/2\"][vc_single_image image=\"2813\" img_size=\"full\" alignment=\"center\"][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][/vc_tta_section][vc_tta_section title=\"MycotoxinTesting\" tab_id=\"ac7\"][vc_row_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/2\"][vc_column_text]</p>\n<h2>Mycotoxins are neurotoxic byproducts produced by certain species of mold and fungus that are commonly found on cannabis</h2>\n<p>They can pose an inherent risk to medical cannabis patients with compromised immune systems. If patients are exposed to mycotoxins over long periods of time, they can accumulate, leading to brain dysfunction or damage. In order to minimize risk to public safety, the state of California has mandated that all cannabis products be tested for the presence of mycotoxins.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/2\"][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][vc_row_inner el_class=\".bg_callout\"][vc_column_inner width=\"1/2\"][vc_column_text]</p>\n<h3>The following is ca list for mycotoxins and their action limits</h3>\n<p>​Mycotoxin testing has been done for food for quite a while, so established methods are well established. The conventional method for mycotoxin detection is HPLC-FLD, which is High performance liquid chromatography paired with a fluorescence detector.[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text][table id=4 /][/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/2\"][vc_single_image image=\"2813\" img_size=\"full\" alignment=\"center\"][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][/vc_tta_section][vc_tta_section title=\"MycotoxinTesting\" tab_id=\"1516669048223-9ac674ee-8c4b\"][vc_row_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/2\"][vc_column_text]</p>\n<h2>Mycotoxins are neurotoxic byproducts produced by certain species of mold and fungus that are commonly found on cannabis</h2>\n<p>They can pose an inherent risk to medical cannabis patients with compromised immune systems. If patients are exposed to mycotoxins over long periods of time, they can accumulate, leading to brain dysfunction or damage. In order to minimize risk to public safety, the state of California has mandated that all cannabis products be tested for the presence of mycotoxins.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/2\"][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][vc_row_inner el_class=\".bg_callout\"][vc_column_inner width=\"1/2\"][vc_column_text]</p>\n<h3>The following is ca list for mycotoxins and their action limits</h3>\n<p>​Mycotoxin testing has been done for food for quite a while, so established methods are well established. The conventional method for mycotoxin detection is HPLC-FLD, which is High performance liquid chromatography paired with a fluorescence detector.[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text][table id=4 /][/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/2\"][vc_single_image image=\"2813\" img_size=\"full\" alignment=\"center\"][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][/vc_tta_section][/vc_tta_accordion][/vc_column][/vc_row]</p>\n', 'Services', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '651-autosave-v1', '', '', '2018-01-23 00:58:16', '2018-01-23 00:58:16', '', 651, 'http://localhost:8888/belcosta/wordpress/2018/01/16/651-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
